  "prompt": "Does a voltmeter show RMS voltage?",
  "response": "The answer depends on the type of voltmeter:\n\n1. Analog voltmeters:\n- Usually show average voltage\n- Require scaling to convert to RMS voltage\n- Typically not directly showing RMS value\n\n2. Digital voltmeters (DMMs):\n- Most modern digital voltmeters display true RMS voltage\n- Can accurately measure RMS value for both sinusoidal and non-sinusoidal waveforms\n- Often have a specific RMS measurement mode\n\n3. Specialized RMS voltmeters:\n- Designed specifically to measure RMS voltage\n- Provide direct, accurate RMS readings\n\nSo, while analog voltmeters typically do not show RMS voltage directly, most modern digital voltmeters do display RMS voltage, especially when set to the appropriate measurement mode.",
